This paper is about color face recognition, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using quaternion-based norms for representation, which is a technique that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). The paper also mentions using high-dimensional representations, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of adaptive representation suggests the possibility of using neural networks (cs.NE) or other adaptive learning techniques.
